	6.5 Limitations on Milestone Payments






	6.5.1 

	No milestone payments are owed for any Milestone Event that is not achieved and in the case where one Option Compound
	or Licensed Product is substituted for another, then the milestones payable with respect to the new Option Compound or Licensed Product are only for future Milestone Events.





	6.5.2 

	Each milestone will be paid only once per Program upon the first achievement of the Milestone Event, regardless of the number of Option Compounds or Licensed Products resulting under the
	Program, and regardless of whether any such Option Compound or Licensed Product constitutes a [...***...] product or any combination of the foregoing. The Discovery Milestone will be paid a maximum of four (4) times, once for each of the
	four (4) Programs, upon the first achievement of such Milestone Event for each Program, and will not be paid again for the Initial Collaboration Targets in the event that either or both such Initial Collaboration Targets are substituted with
	other Targets pursuant to Section 3.2.





